			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Well once you get into higher levels I think Shamans should reconsider reusing this spell. I am level 28 and I still use this spell when I solo. Often I have just a smidge of mana left at the end of a solo fight that isn't enough to power my main spells. You would be surprised though how many Frost Rifts you can cast with that tiny amount of mana. Its just a easy way to utilize ALL you mana in a fight and this tactic has actually saved me quite a few times. When you get to the end of a solo fight it usually comes down to the wire and this will get you over.
				</font>
