	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				I think I know what Predaturs is talking about when he said the spell cancels the melee.  While casting, your attack is temporarily suspended (you can't do both at once).  Once your spell goes off, then you have to wait for the delay time again before you strike in melee.  You've effectively added the casting time of the spell to the weapons delay time for the bonus that you will be hitting twice (one with spell, one with melee).  since the speed factor to damage ratio of this spell is better than the hammer, you aren't really losing anything.  As for chain casting and missing melee completely, you can't really unless you have a really quick spell and really slow weapon.  The recast delay on the spells will usually allow you to get a hit in edgewise, even if you are trying not to and even if you are using a Bloodforge hammer.  <BR>
<BR>
PS.  IMHO the RTS is still better than the Bloodforge.  You have a great damage/delay ratio for spellcasters and you get +5 hp and +5 mana.  Not much but every bit helps.
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
