	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				This spell works well in combat and gives you quite an edge, so long as it's cast right.<BR>
First, cast drowsy on the opponent so that they attack (and interrupt spellcasting)less frequently.<BR>
Then, wait until immediatly after the opponent attacks - then quickly fire it off.<BR>
Hopefully you can fire the spell inbetween the attacks, and watch out for those bashes.<BR>
With this you can do massive combined melee/spell damage (especially with a good weapon) that is pretty cool for a few levels.
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
